WEBVTT

00:14:28.427 --> 00:14:30.773
My responsibility
is to get you home rich."

00:14:30.797 --> 00:14:32.261
(Laughter)

00:14:32.285 --> 00:14:34.491
You want to get home alive,
that's on you."

00:14:34.515 --> 00:14:37.143
And for the rest
of that day -- safety first.

00:14:37.167 --> 00:14:38.810
I mean, I was like --

00:14:38.834 --> 00:14:45.144
So, the idea that we create
this sense of complacency

00:14:45.168 --> 00:14:49.667
when all we do is talk
about somebody else's responsibility

00:14:49.691 --> 00:14:51.624
as though it's our own, and vice versa.

00:14:51.648 --> 00:14:53.270
Anyhow, a whole lot of things.

00:14:53.294 --> 00:14:56.721
I could talk at length
about the many little distinctions we made

00:14:56.745 --> 00:14:59.601
and the endless list of ways
that I got it wrong.

00:14:59.625 --> 00:15:01.960
But what it all comes down to is this: